Claims What is claimed is: 1. An article of footwear, comprising: an upper; and a sole attached to the upper, the upper and sole forming an interior void; and a control device comprising a button module, the button module comprising: a raised standoff assembly comprising a first standoff portion and a second standoff portion, wherein the first standoff portion is joined to the second standoff portion by an intermediate standoff portion; and a circuit board including a panel portion, the panel portion including a first button a second button, the first and second buttons mounted on the panel portion, wherein the raised standoff assembly is secured on the panel portion of the circuit board; wherein the first standoff portion includes a first annular ridge that surrounds the first button the first annular ridge having a first ridge height that is at least as high as a first button height of the first button; wherein the second standoff portion includes a second annular ridge that surrounds the second button the button module being disposed adjacent to an inner surface of the upper within the interior void of the article of footwear. 2. The article of footwear according to claim 1, wherein the second annular ridge has a second ridge height that is at least as high as a second button height of the second button. 3. The article of footwear according to any one of claims 1 and 2, wherein the control device further comprises a wiring portion coupling the button module to an auto-lacing system. 4. The article of footwear according to any one of claims 1 and 2, wherein the button module comprises a first portion, a second portion, and a bridge portion extending between the first portion and the second portion, wherein the bridge portion has a bridge width smaller than a first width of the first portion and a second width of the second portion. 5. The article of footwear according to claim 4, wherein the first portion of the button module includes the first standoff portion and the first button, and wherein the second portion of the button module includes the second standoff portion and the second button. 6. The article of footwear according to claim 4, further comprising: a sleeve attached to an inner surface of the upper and configured to receive and secure the button module in the interior void of the article of footwear. 7. The article of footwear according to claim 6, wherein the bridge portion is enclosed in the sleeve. 8. The article of footwear according to any one of claims 1 and 2, wherein the button module is disposed adjacent to and beneath a button region of the upper, and wherein the button region is configured to extend over the button module from a first end of the button module to a second end of the button module. 9. The article of footwear according to claim 8, wherein the button region of the upper is stretched to a greater degree in a tensioned state relative to a loosened state, and wherein the button region exerts a substantially similar force on the first button in the tensioned state as in the loosened state. 10. An article of footwear, comprising: an upper including an outer layer that forms an interior void; and a sole structure secured to the upper; 

 a button module, comprising a first portion, a second portion, a bridge portion joining first portion to the second portion, and a circuit board, the circuit board including a panel portion the button module being disposed under the outer layer of the upper, wherein the bridge portion has a bridge width that is less than a first width of the first portion and the bridge portion permits the first portion to move relative to the second portion; a first button and a second button, each mounted on the panel portion of the circuit board; and a raised standoff assembly secured to the panel portion of the circuit board, the raised standoff assembly comprising a first standoff portion, a second standoff portion, and an intermediate standoff portion joining the first standoff portion to the second standoff portion, the first standoff portion including a first annular ridge that surrounds the first button, the second standoff portion including a second annular ridge that surrounds the second button. 11. The article of footwear according to claim 10, wherein the second portion has a second width and the wherein the bridge width is less than the second width. 12. The article of footwear according to any one of claims 10 and 11, wherein the first portion includes the first standoff portion and the first button, and wherein the second portion of the button module includes the second standoff portion and the second button. 13. The article of footwear according to any one of claims 10 and 11, wherein the raised standoff assembly further includes a lip portion extending along a peripheral edge of the raised standoff assembly, and wherein the lip portion surrounds an outer edge of the panel portion. 14. The article of footwear according to any one of claims 10 and 11, wherein the bridge portion permits the first portion to torsionally twist relative to the second portion. 15. The article of footwear according to any one of claims 10 and 11, wherein the bridge portion permits the first portion and the second portion to each bend in a downward direction. 16. A method, comprising: aligning a first standoff portion of a raised standoff assembly of a control device with a first button of a panel portion of a circuit board of the control device and aligning a second standoff portion of the raised standoff assembly with a second button of the panel portion; mounting the raised standoff assembly on the panel portion of the circuit board by stretching an outer border of the raised standoff assembly to surround and capture an outer edge of the panel portion; circumferentially surrounding the first button with a first annular ridge of the first standoff portion, the first button and the first annular ridge having a substantially similar height; circumferentially surrounding the second button with a second annular ridge of the second standoff portion; securing the control device to a portion of an upper of an article of footwear; and arranging an outer layer of the upper across an uppermost surface of the first annular ridge such that the outer layer extends over the first button, thereby inhibiting the outer layer of the upper from exerting pressure against the first button. 17. The method of claim 16, further comprising attaching a stiffener to a lower surface of the control device. 18. The method of any one of claims 16 and 17, wherein securing the control device comprises inserting the control device into a sleeve that is attached to the outer layer of the upper. 19. The method of any one of claims 16 and 17, further comprising attaching texture elements on a button region of the outer layer, wherein 

 the button region is disposed above the first button and the second button. 20. The method of any one of claims 16 and 17, further comprising connecting a wiring portion of the control device to an auto-lacing system in the article of footwear.
